Healthcare Services of AmericaInc said its chairman and chief executive officer, CharlesSpeir, resigned and its president and chief operating officer,Thomas Rodgaers Jr, was relieved of his duties.    Michael Cronin will take over as chairman and MichaelMurphy as acting president and chief executive officer, thecompany said.    Cronin has been a director of the company since 1983 andMurphy has been a consultant to the compay, Healthcare Servicessaid. Reuter&#3;